## 🚀 Getting Started

These instructions will help you get the frontend app running locally.

### ✅ Prerequisites

- Node.js (v16 or higher)
- npm or yarn
- `.env` file (see `.env_sample` for reference)

---

### 📦 Installation

```bash
git clone <%= repository %>
cd <%= full_project_name %>
npm install
````

Or with Yarn:

```bash
yarn install
```

---

### 🧪 Development Server

```bash
npm run dev
```

Tailwind watcher:

```bash
npm run devcss
```

This will launch the app on:
`http://localhost:<%= port || 5173 %>`

---

### 🏗️ Production Build

```bash
npm run build
```

This will output your production-ready files into the `dist/` directory.

